					<td width="335" height="145" colspan="1" rowspan="1" valign="top" align="left" xpos="300" content bgcolor="#ffe39f" csheight="145"><font size="4"><img src="/web/20090330145729im_/http://www.st-benoit-du-lac.com/images/b.gif" width="37" height="38" align="BOTTOM" naturalsizeflag="3"> </font><font size="3"><b>enedictine life having disappeared in France at the Revolution flourished anew in 1833 with Dom Prosper Gu&eacute;ranger. He was a young priest imbued with deep faith and with an acute sense of the needs of the Church. With the help of God, he undertook to restore the monastic life in the ancient Priory Saint-Pierre de-Solesmes. In 1853, with his first disciples, he was able to give new life to the venerable Abbey of Ligug&eacute;, which in turn restored the Abbey of Saint-Wandrille in Normandy, hence comes Saint-Beno&icirc;t-du-Lac.</b></font></td>
